==English==

===Phrase===

'''pleating to the sett'''

# A system of pleating a [[kilt]] in which one full [[sett]] of the [[tartan]] pattern is taken up in each pleat, resulting in a reproduction of the pattern across the back of the kilt. Cp: [[pleating to the stripe]]

===Reference===

# Barbara Tewksbury and Elsie Stuehmeyer, ''The Art of Kiltmaking'' (Celtic Dragon Press, Deansboro, NY, 2001, ISBN 0-9703751-0-7)

